---
import '../../styles/sections/about.css';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../../components/ui/SectionHeader.astro';
import Divider from '../../components/global/Divider.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Qi-Lab" description="Learn about Qi-Lab's brand story, philosophy, and contact information.">
  <div class="about-page">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Page Hero -->
      <section class="page-hero" data-reveal>
        <span class="page-label">// ABOUT</span>
        <h1 class="page-title">About Qi-Lab</h1>
        <p class="page-subtitle">
          A personal brand focused on technology, design, and creativity
        </p>
      </section>

      <Divider />

      <!-- Brand Story -->
      <section class="about-section" data-reveal>
        <SectionHeader label="// STORY" title="Brand Story" />
        <div class="about-prose">
          <p>
            The name Qi-Lab comes from the understanding of two Chinese characters: "Qi" represents the pursuit of beautiful things, 
            while "Yan" represents the persistent exploration of technical depth. Combined, they form a creative laboratory dedicated to finding balance between code and aesthetics.
          </p>
          <p>
            We focus on three intersecting areas: frontend engineering, system design, and creative experiments. In our daily practice, we use 
            Astro to build high-performance static sites, design tokens to maintain visual consistency, 
            and structured knowledge management methods (Notion + Obsidian dual-track system) to accumulate technical thinking. 
            Every project is a validation of the "engineering aesthetics" concept.
          </p>
          <p>
            Here, we are not satisfied with just writing code that works. Every line of code carries a pursuit of elegance, 
            and every design decision is carefully considered. From pixel-level visual polishing to system-level architectural thinking, 
            Qi-Lab always adheres to the craftsmanship spirit of "continuous improvement". We believe that technology is not a cold tool, 
            but a medium for expressing creativity — good engineers are also good artists, 
            who draw blueprints with code and weave dreams with logic.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <Divider />

      <!-- Philosophy -->
      <section class="about-section" data-reveal>
        <SectionHeader label="// PHILOSOPHY" title="Design Philosophy" />
        <div class="philosophy-grid">
          <div class="philosophy-card">
            <span class="philosophy-number">01</span>
            <h3 class="philosophy-title">Warm Physicality</h3>
            <p class="philosophy-desc">
              The oat gray background is like warm paper, with emerald green and amber gold accents like hand-drawn marks. 
              We pursue physical texture in digital interfaces — the layering of frosted glass, the warmth of paper textures, 
              and the rhythm of light and shadow flow. Every interaction should make people feel "carefully designed".
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="philosophy-card">
            <span class="philosophy-number">02</span>
            <h3 class="philosophy-title">Code as Art</h3>
            <p class="philosophy-desc">
              Code is not just a functional implementation, but also a creative expression. 
              We use CSS custom properties to build 300+ design tokens, Astro's Islands Architecture 
              to achieve zero-redundancy interactions, and Playwright to ensure every commit stands the test. 
              Readability, maintainability, and aesthetics are all essential.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="philosophy-card">
            <span class="philosophy-number">03</span>
            <h3 class="philosophy-title">Continuous Exploration</h3>
            <p class="philosophy-desc">
              Technology is constantly evolving, and learning never ends. The migration from Next.js to Astro allowed us to rediscover the 
              value of "zero JS by default", and the transition from Tailwind to design tokens helped us grasp the essence of visual consistency. 
              Maintain curiosity, be brave to try new technologies, and continue to grow through practice.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <Divider />

      <!-- Contact CTA -->
      <section class="about-section" data-reveal>
        <SectionHeader label="// CONTACT" title="Get in Touch" />
        <div class="contact-cta">
          <p class="cta-text">
            Whether it's technical cooperation, project consultation, or just a chat about technology and design, 
            feel free to contact Qi-Lab through the following methods.
          </p>
          <div class="cta-links">
            <a href="mailto:hello@qi-lab.dev" class="cta-link">
              <span class="cta-label">Email</span>
              <span class="cta-value">hello@qi-lab.dev</span>
            </a>
            <div class="cta-link">
              <span class="cta-label">WeChat</span>
              <span class="cta-value">QiLab_Studio</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <a href="/en#contact" class="cta-btn">View Full Contact Information</a>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>